.TH wxDisplayChangedEvent 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxDisplayChangedEvent \- A display changed event is sent to top-level windows when the display resolution has changed.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This event is currently emitted under Windows only.

.PP
See: \fIwxDisplay\fR

.PP
This class is derived, and can use functions, from:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxEvent\fR

.RE

.PP
wxWidgets docs: wxDisplayChangedEvent

.SS "Events"

.PP
Use \fIwxEvtHandler:connect/3\fR with \fIwxDisplayChangedEventType\fR to subscribe to events of this type.

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBwxDisplayChanged() :: #wxDisplayChanged{}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBwxDisplayChangedEvent() :: wx:wx_object().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBwxDisplayChangedEventType() :: display_changed.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
